name: Warung Seni
address: Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
types: restaurant, vegan_restaurant, pizza_restaurant, vegetarian_restaurant, food, store
review 1:
Love this place!
Food, service, atmosphere were the best! Quiet place to relax in shadow under the bright sun.
Personal is very friendly. We came here 3 times and it became our favorite place in this area.
review 2: Super delicious vegan hamburger and cauliflower with great sauce. Everyone else loved their food too! Yum ‚ò∫Ô∏è
review 3:
The ambiente is impressive. I had the impression like entering a botanical garden. Flowers and green all over. Tables and benches on hidden places. Lovely.

The food was great looking, the taste was a bit disapointing. The very first time in Bali that I had to add spices. The same for the juices, not really tasty and small. But the dessert was great.

A shop for Bali souveniers in high quality for reasonable prices is also included.

It's a place made for foreign tourists, presenting them the paradise athmosphere of Bali.
review 4: The best! Organic, healthy, vegan High quality comfort food! I loved it so Much! Stone oven glutenfree pizza and delicious fried noodles! Fun to try the tropical pizza with fruits and cinnamon! So Good! Sweetest staff and delivery take away option. Thank you! Will be back!
review 5: It kinda decent size restaurant but it‚Äôs far from noisy street, perfect for hang out and I prefer the grilled fish than fish & chips. They provide you with several fan in almost every corner, location is neat, artsy, & clean, other than that I still recommend this location.

name: Gaia-Oasis Beach Resort
address: Jalan Singaraja-Amlapura, Dusun Tegal Sumaga, Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
A magical place! Significantly less touristy compared to Ubud/Kuta/Sanur, etc...

The spa services were incredible, and the restaurant dishes out some incredible food as well. The dishes varied from western to Indonesian menu items. I only ordered indonesian options and they were all quite nice and appropriately seasoned and spiced (I'm Indonesian fyi).

I would come by for a longer visit without a doubt.
review 2: We were honored to spend time here !!!!   So so beautiful.....   BEST spot.....   amazing people.....   so clean....so safe....   fantastic buffets !!!!
review 3:
Gaia is a gem. A piece of heaven on earth.
We stayed at Abasan (mountain) and Patai (ocean) and loved both experiences.

I can highly recommend this resort to stay or run a retreat.

The staff is super friendly.
The food delicious.

‚Ä¶ and they might not tell you but this resort supports many ngos, has a massive positive impact on Bali.

I cannot wait to be back as this place has stolen a piece of my heart
review 4: Staying here has truly been a breathtaking and transformative experience. I truly feel changed for the better and I am only half way thru my time here. The staff tends to you like divine family, the spirituality and prayers here are healing. I have never been taken care of like I have here. Any concerns are addressed immediately. Plus, the foundation does incredible work. Thank you for my time and transformation here. I will visit again and again. üôè‚ú®üåäüåÖ
review 5: The resort and staff is so kind, conscious, and tender. Hearts are full, open, strong, and clear. Body is nourished, mind is relaxed, soul is connected. Ms. Putu and Eta provided such a divine stay. The island of the gods as Yen would say. I felt so held and healed here. All of the departments had their specialty and did a spectacular job no matter what the need was. Any time there was a challenge it was cleared up quickly. I feel so grateful to have had the honor of staying here. I cannot wait to come back, home.

name: Villa Aditya Tejakula
address: V9F2+JXM, Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
A great place to stay in this region. Very quiet and nice swimming pool. The rooms are very clean and tidy.
The personal are so kind and friendly!
The garden is beautiful and they even have a beautiful yoga space!
Watching the sunrise at the back of the hotel is stunning!
We recommend this hotel!
review 2: Such a lovely place and excellent value for money. We love Tejakula and Villa Aditya is right next to the beach in a gorgeous garden. Rooms are well equipped, staff are lovely and breakfasts are great.
review 3:
Beautiful place run by local people, very friendly, available, attentive and smiling. Beautiful gardens and facilities, very close to the beach. The rooms are very spacious, bright and air-conditioned with a large terrace with dining area and lounge chair. Large kitchen equipped with the basics but with drinking water dispenser and fridge (important for ice cold beers). You also have a hot shower (who wants a hot shower in Indonesia?). The room is cleaned daily. You can have breakfast on your terrace or in the dining room overlooking the sea, I highly recommend this one because it is plentiful, made with local products and very good value for money compared to other places nearby. Spa and restaurants nearby for lunch and dinner. Supermarkets and ATM within 20 minutes walk.
You can also do yoga in a specially designed place as well as massages. They organized all our trips and departure from the place with driver with perfect English . There is also the important detail of providing you with repellent for the body and for the rooms because of the mosquitoes (it is in the middle of the jungle and it is Indonesian) and a big umbrella for your use in case of rain. For the service and value for money I absolutely recommend it.
review 4:
Made and team are all very helpful. If you‚Äôre looking for a quiet getaway, here is perfect. You can rent a scooter straight from Made for a reasonable price, rooms cleaned everyday. The nearby restaurants Warung seni and Warung made are delicious and have enough options to go to multiple times. Everyone there is very friendly. The beach is literally 30 seconds walk from my room. You can hear the waves from your outside daybed.
Highly recommend
review 5:
I enjoyed my stay here.
It is very quiet.
There isn‚Äôt much in the area so I would recommend to go to the next door warung: Warung Seni for your meals.
It is a perfect place to chill, hang by the pool and do some yoga (self-practice).
You can walk straight to the beach (peddles not sand)

name: Camplung Beach Villa
address: Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1: This is an amazing property with amazing and helpful staff. Everything you could want in a facility. The beach is a rock beach, but the waters contain lots of sea life easily accessible by snorkeling within 30 50 feet of the shoreline. Plan your shopping before you get there, don't hesitate to book a ride somewhere. Friendly and helpful drivers.
review 2: It was one of the best vacations my family has taken.  If you're looking for a slower feel, this is the spot.   The staff are amazing, and we honestly didn't want to leave.
review 3: Wonderful villa to vacation with your family or friends. The staff are very helpful and courteous. Direct access to the ocean.
review 4: Stayed over a week at Camplung Beach Villa with a large group of family. The photos don't do it justice, it is a beautifully built villa situated right on the waterfront. The staff are extremely friendly and accommodating. I would stay there again if I ever get the chance.
review 5:
It's been an amazing time!
Villa very spacious, friendly staff and amazing hosts.
Highly recommended, especially if you got small kids. So easy to keep them entertained either in the play house, beach, pool or big lawn.
Thank you so much

name: The Lumbung Tejakula
address: Dusun Tegal Sumaga, Desa, Tejakula, Kec. Tejakula, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
The Lumbung Tejakula makes for the most delightful stay. The cabins are all of soft scented wood, very tasteful and have everything you will need.  The bathroom is open to the skies, which is lovely, with hot water and nicely decorated. The porch has comfy chairs with cushions and, best of all, looks out on to a most beautiful garden.
Mega keeps this lovely homely property immaculately clean and real credit to her, her father and family for creating this wonderful accommodation. The attention to detail is second to none. A more peaceful and relaxing time you will not find even in the best places in Bali. Did I mention the access to the beach? You step out of the gardens, through a wonderful gateway and you are on manicured lawns covered in palms right to the sea. Mega (father) is a creative artist who has worked hard to help make this property an idyllic sanctuary. Mega (daughter) is a ray of sunshine who will look after all your needs, she is the perfect host. Mother places the ceremonial "chanang Sari" and fills the place with the delicious smell of incense. Enjoy!
‚ù§Ô∏è
review 2:
Nice clean rooms with good aircon and good shower.
Beautiful garden area.
Direct at the beach with nice snorkling.
Mega is very helpfull and friendly.
You can get breakfast just next door at Gaia-Oasis for a reasonable price.
Close by is an other nice warung.
We also recommend the dolphin tour with local fisherman.
review 3: Went there for my birthday trip... it's memorable. Great location. Great beach. Amazing service - the owner rode with me to the local salt farm, they lent us snorkeling equipments. Literally sad to leave after 2 nights..
review 4: Really nice place to stay, comfortable rooms,   nice staff, right on the beach and a complete share kitchen if you wouldike to cook up your own food
review 5: Sea front property, with gorgeous newly renovated villas and a kitchen, bar and seating area. The place is peaceful. Family run accommodation, very friendly and helpful. I was very sad to leave as it was beautiful there. Good hot shower, big bed, wifi worked well. There was a nearby warung for food in walking distance.

name: Pranajaya Villa
address: Jl. Dolphin No.14, Tejakula, Kec. Tejakula, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
You enter a country road all the way to the end near the uninhabited sea.  (not the beach with fine sand) but very pretty views of the calm ocean without tourists.  There is no service desk in this small hotel but people and gardeners pass by from time to time during the day very discreetly we are very comfortable like at home.  It is a very local place with 4 small independent nests.  There is a swimming pool in the center of the garden with many subtropical green trees and flowers and a terrace for each little nest in the room.  large space.The bathroom sink wc and an open-air Italian shower üöø has no roof and you can see the blue sky, white clouds and tall coconut trees when you take a üöø shower It has  a fully equipped shared kitchen.  Breakfast of fresh fruit drinks is specially delivered to your terrace every morning, JAY The boss will also come and ask if you need anything despite his busy schedule.  JAY added you on WhatsApp to communicate with each other and you can communicate directly at any time if necessary. It's very practical.  here It is a very quiet paradise far from the city but close to the sea. If you stay for a long time you can rent a motorbike for easy access wherever you want..
Merci beaucoup JAY  üëíüíûüíûüíû
review 2:
it is so wonderful! so green! There are three rooms for rent in this garden, so it is quiet and private. it is so beautiful! just look at the pictures...it's even more beautiful in real life!

Ôøº
review 3:
I love the concept! Back to natureüíöü§çüíö
So green and quiet place.
But hopefully the room will be kept more clean.
review 4: Nice location close to the beach with a lot of wildlife. This is the perfect oasis for relaxation. The bungalows and the pool area are very nice and tidy. The owner is a true service man, and he will take great care of you while you are there. The breakfast, which is included, is good. Highly recommend this place, located in a not that touristy part of Bali!
review 5: Jay is a great host and has a great residence. Clean, private and close to the beach. Jay can organise everything including dolphin watching, priest cleansing and many more. Both thumbs up from me.

name: halumba eco villa
address: Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1: Absolutely serene experience. Everything were perfect, thanks to Pak Made and his team for all the hospitality, cleanliness, and whole-hearted service. We went there on New Year's eve till the 1st ofJanuary 2024. I love all the details of the premises, awesome pool and its cute dolphin statue. It just took a very short walk to the pristine Tejakula's beach. Definitely would be there again.
review 2: I started with booking for 2 days. I ended up staying for 6 days. I absolutely loved it here. The owner keeps the facilities clean . You are tucked away from the main road with walking distance to the ocean. There is a beautiful outside pool, that is also kept clean. It is a short distance to in town with delicious food and fruit stands. If you are feeling adventurous, there is a waterfall close by to visit. I also woke up early around 2 am and was able to drive and hike up Mt Batur by sunrise! If your looking for a good place to stay at the right price this is your spot. I know you will enjoy it as much as I did. Hope to be back soon! Thank you for your hospitality!!
review 3: Peaceful place, nice ambiance, very comfy place to have holiday with family . Highly Recommended villa . Short distance to the beach and the city ‚ú®‚ú®
review 4: A relaxing and quiet bungalow hotel in Tejakula. We stayed here for a couple of days and really enjoyed the weather, the beach and the bungalows. The accommodation has everything you need and its nice to swim in the pool late at night. 10/10 would stay again. If you want to do more then just relax you can learn about Lemurian Healing and visiting the temple in Tejakula gives a nice view of the area.
review 5:
We didn‚Äôt plan to, but stayed at Halumba for almost a week! The villa was beautiful, new, clean, neat. Shower was very clean and pleasant, linen and bed clean and comfy, good AC, and a lovely balcony overlooking a pool shared with only two other bungalows...

Dedek and his family were very helpful and sweet, helping to organize anything, giving great tips for the area, and the breakfast was great! We also had access to the kitchen, to make coffee etc, which was a great plus.

We‚Äôd definitely stay again if we‚Äôre in the area!

name: Bahari villa Tejakula
address: V9C4+V98, Tejakula, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
My second stay at this gorgeous villa.
A pleasure to be welcomed back by Ibu Wayan and Gede.
They were so helpful and kind when we had troubles with our vehicle, they even shared a meal with us at Dapur Bali Murah which was an beautiful experience.
The villa is perfectly positioned near the ocean, very well equipped, a fabulous cold pool (rare in Bali!) and I couldn't be happier sharing it with a friend and can't wait to visit again. Thankyou!
review 2: One villa for that price? Fantastic! Only 1 star down is the breakfest and no TV but the price is really great for what you get and for 1 night we stayed no TV was needed.
review 3: Barari Villa is absolutely BEAUTIFUL!!! Wayan and Budi are amazing hosts that treat you like family. The villa is situated only steps from the black rock beach and the sound of the gentle surf can be heard from the comfortable beds as we slept.  Everything was very clean and well maintained. This is the perfect spot to get away from the crowds of Ubud and to experience the peace and joy that Bali and her people have to offer!
review 4:
Greatest place I've ever stayed at for this price. The owner Wayan is so nice and considerate. If you are a person who never want to leave this ridiculously luxurious villa (which we are not) you won't have to. They offer you everything you can think of without cheating you about the cost or anything. Best experience we ever had and I've travel all around the world. Negative reviews of this place is beyond reason. Wayan, bodi and goodday. We love you ‚ù§Ô∏è

Adam, Martin and Lovisa
